==== US/Russian war causes extinction – most probable ====&#xD;
&#xD;
(% class=&amp;#34;MinimizedText&amp;#34; %)&#xD;
Nick (% class=&amp;#34;StyleStyleBold12pt&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size:13.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt&amp;#34; %)Bostrom(%%), professor of philosophy - Oxford University, March, (% class=&amp;#34;StyleStyleBold12pt&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size:13.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt&amp;#34; %)2002(%%), Existential Risks: Analyzing Human Extinction Scenarios and Related Hazards, Journal of Evolution and Technology, p. http:~/~/www.nickbostrom.com/existential/risks.html(% class=&amp;#34;MinimizedTextChar&amp;#34; %)A much greater existential risk emerged with the build-up of nuclear arsenals in the US and the USSR. (% style=&amp;#34;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow&amp;#34; %)__An __(% class=&amp;#34;CircledChar&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow&amp;#34; %)all-out nuclear war(% style=&amp;#34;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow&amp;#34; %)__ was__(%%)__ a possibility with__(% class=&amp;#34;MinimizedTextChar&amp;#34; %) both (% style=&amp;#34;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow&amp;#34; %)__a __(% class=&amp;#34;CircledChar&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow&amp;#34; %)substantial probability(% style=&amp;#34;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow&amp;#34; %)__ and with consequences that__(% class=&amp;#34;MinimizedTextChar&amp;#34; %) might have been persistent enough to (% style=&amp;#34;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow&amp;#34; %)__qualify as __(% class=&amp;#34;CircledChar&amp;#34; %)global and terminal(%%). (% class=&amp;#34;MinimizedTextChar&amp;#34; %)There was a real worry among those best acquainted with the information available at the time that(%%) (% style=&amp;#34;background:yellow;mso-highlight: yellow&amp;#34; %)__a nuclear Armageddon__(% class=&amp;#34;MinimizedTextChar&amp;#34; %) would occur and that it (% style=&amp;#34;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow&amp;#34; %)__might __(% class=&amp;#34;CircledChar&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow&amp;#34; %)annihilate our species(% class=&amp;#34;MinimizedTextChar&amp;#34; %) or permanently destroy human civilization.4(%%)  (% style=&amp;#34;background:yellow;mso-highlight: yellow&amp;#34; %)__Russia and the US retain large nuclear arsenals__(%%)__ that (% style=&amp;#34;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow&amp;#34; %)could be used in a future confrontation(%%)__(% class=&amp;#34;MinimizedTextChar&amp;#34; %), either accidentally or deliberately. There is also a risk that other states may one day build up large nuclear arsenals. Note however that (% style=&amp;#34;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow&amp;#34; %)__a smaller nuclear exchange__(% class=&amp;#34;MinimizedTextChar&amp;#34; %), between India and Pakistan for instance,(%%) (% style=&amp;#34;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow&amp;#34; %)__is not an __(% class=&amp;#34;CircledChar&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow&amp;#34; %)existential risk(%%)__, since it would not destroy__ (% class=&amp;#34;MinimizedTextChar&amp;#34; %)or thwart(%%) __humankind__(% class=&amp;#34;MinimizedTextChar&amp;#34; %)’s potential permanently. Such a war might however be a local terminal risk for the cities most likely to be targeted. Unfortunately, we shall see that nuclear Armageddon and comet or asteroid strikes are mere preludes to the existential risks that we will encounter in the 21st century.&#xD;
